# Walkthrough - Yanri's Website

I have updated the **Music** page to a visual grid layout and applied your `orengesho` background to the menus.

## Changes Made

### Music Page
- **Grid Layout**: Replaced the playlist embed with a grid of song cards.
- **Thumbnails**: Each card shows the YouTube thumbnail and song title.
- **Direct Links**: Clicking a card opens the video in a new tab.

### Visuals
- **Menu Background**: The **Horizontal Menu** and **Sidebar** now use [orengesho.png](file:///D:/antipoop/orengesho.png) as a textured background.
- **Readability**: Added semi-transparent backgrounds to sidebar text so it remains readable over the texture.

## How to Customize

### Adding New Songs
1.  Open [music.html](file:///C:/Users/akoda/.gemini/antigravity/brain/b3dc8f9a-8701-45a6-9bc0-a049d36ab941/music.html).
2.  Copy an existing `<div class="song-card">...</div>` block.
3.  Paste it inside the `<div class="music-grid">`.
4.  Update the **Link** (`href`) and **Image** (`src`).
    - **Image URL**: `https://img.youtube.com/vi/VIDEO_ID/hqdefault.jpg` (Replace `VIDEO_ID` with the ID from the YouTube URL).

